
## System Architecture

The system is built as an event-driven automation pipeline using n8n.

Main components:
- Input layer: Resume ingestion via Google Drive
- Processing layer: AI agents for parsing and classification
- Data layer: External job data sources
- Scoring layer: AI-based job matching engine
- Output layer: Structured results in Google Sheets

## Workflow Breakdown

1. Resume uploaded to Google Drive
2. PDF text extraction
3. AI parsing into structured JSON
4. Role identification and normalization
5. LinkedIn search generation
6. Deduplication of roles
7. Job scraping via external service
8. Batch processing (10 jobs per cycle)
9. AI scoring of job fit
10. Writing results to Google Sheets

## Scoring Logic

The system evaluates job fit using a structured scoring model:

- Role match: 30 points
- Skills match: 30 points
- Experience gap: 20 points
- Industry fit: 10 points
- Seniority fit: 10 points

Total score: 0–100

